# 📊 Retail Sales SQL Analysis Project

## 🔹 Project Overview
This project analyzes a retail sales dataset using SQL.  
The objective is to extract business insights using queries, joins, aggregations, and advanced SQL functions.

---

## 🔹 Database Tables

- customers  
- orders  
- order_items  
- products  
- shipping  

---

## 🔹 SQL Concepts Used

- SELECT, WHERE, GROUP BY, ORDER BY  
- INNER JOIN (multi-table queries)  
- Aggregate Functions (SUM, COUNT, AVG)  
- CASE statements  
- Window Functions (RANK, LAG)  
- Date Functions (YEAR, MONTH, DATEDIFF)  

---

## 🔹 Key SQL Analysis

### 1. Data Exploration
- Total orders, customers, products  
- Revenue calculation  
- Average Order Value (AOV)  
- Monthly revenue trend  
- Top states by revenue  

### 2. Customer Analysis
- New vs returning customers  
- Top customers by spending  
- Customer churn (inactive users)  

### 3. Product Analysis
- Best-selling products  
- Category-wise revenue  
- Profit calculation  
- Underperforming products  

### 4. Shipping Analysis
- Average shipping time  
- Shipping cost analysis  
- Delayed shipments  

### 5. Advanced SQL
- Customer ranking using RANK()  
- Previous order tracking using LAG()  

---

## 🔹 Additional Insights

- Customer Lifetime Value (CLV)  
- Monthly revenue growth  
- Payment method analysis  
- Discount impact on sales  

